outputs.output_descr: Sustainable forest management secures ecosystem and biodiversity values while providing a buffer to the Congolian Rain Forest, ensuring food security and sustainable livelihoods. The objective is to enable miombo dependent communities to adopt productive practices that are favorable to biodiversity conservation and reduce carbon emissions from land use change and improve livelihoods.

project_descr: Mainstreaming Sustainable Forest Management in the Miombo Woodlands of Western Tanzania.
project_title: Mainstream Sustainable Forest Management In the  Miombo
